# Filter Configuration for clangd-call-tree

# This file defines which paths are included or excluded from call tree analysis.
#
# Format:
# +pattern - Include paths matching this pattern
# -pattern - Exclude paths matching this pattern
#
# Rules are processed in order: first match wins.
# If no rules match, path is included by default.
#
# Patterns:
# src/ - Match directory and all subdirectories
# *.cpp - Match all .cpp files
# test_*.c - Match files starting with test_
# /absolute/path - Match absolute path
#
# Lines starting with # are comments.

# Include main source directories
+src/

# Exclude test files
-test_*

# Exclude build directories
-.pio/
-.vscode/
-build/

# Exclude third-party libraries
-3rdparty/
-vendor/
-external/
